Package kodkod.util

Interface Summary
IndexedEntry<E> Represents an entry in a sparse sequence.
IntIterator Represents an iterator over int primitives.
IntSet Represents an ordered set of integers.
SparseSequence<V> Represents a sparse sequence -- a sequence whose indeces are not necessarily contiguous.
 

Class Summary
AbstractIndexedEntry<V> A skeletal implementation of the IndexedEntry interface.
AbstractIntSet A skeletal implementation of the IntSet interface.
AbstractSparseSequence<V> A skeletal implementation of the SparseSequence interface.
ArraySequence<V> An implementation of a sparse sequence based on an array.
ArrayStack<T> A Stack implementation based on an array.
IdentityHashSet<T> This class implements the Set interface with a hash table, using reference-equality in place of object-equality when comparing elements.
IntBitSet An implementation of the IntSet interface based on a bit map.
IntRange Represents a range of integers, [min..max].
Ints This class contains various utility methods for working with integers, IntRanges, and IntSets.
IntTreeSet An implementation of the IntTreeSet interface based on a balanced binary search tree.
Iterators This class provides utility methods for constructing iterators.
LinkedStack<T> A Stack implementation based on a singly linked list.
Stack<T> Represents a last-in-first-out (LIFO) stack of objects.
TreeSequence<V> An implementation of a sparse sequence based on a balanced binary search tree.
